<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2890] binary data may lose bytes with JSON transport under specific circumstances</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2890</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Delphi implementation currently relies on IdCoderMIME for base64 encoding/decoding, which expects the base64 encoding to be complete with padding. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With Thrift it is legal to transfer binary data via JSON without padding, but IdCoderMIME fails to handle this case correctly. Depending on the length of the data, up to 2 bytes from the end of a binary data block may get lost.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12761583">THRIFT-2890</key>
            <summary>binary data may lose bytes with JSON transport under specific circumstances</summary>
